DeseqDataSet ( ) 8000 rlog(dds) 

dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = counts, 
                              colData = conditions,
                              design = ~ tissue + cells)
dds <- dds[names(sort(rowSums(counts(dds)), decreasing = TRUE)[1:8000]), ] #  8000   

dds <- DESeq(dds)
## estimating size factors
## estimating dispersions
## gene-wise dispersion estimates
## mean-dispersion relationship
## final dispersion estimates
## fitting model and testing
## -- replacing outliers and refitting for 192 genes
## -- DESeq argument 'minReplicatesForReplace' = 7 
## -- original counts are preserved in counts(dds)
## estimating dispersions
## fitting model and testing
#dds <- vst(dds) 
dds_log<- rlog(dds) #  blind    blind ,  sort   order
#   DESeqTransform  DESeqDataSetFromMatrix 
counts.norm <- assay(dds_log)

cor ( mm, m ) 1 - cor, dist hclust, : average, complete and single

dds_cor <- cor(counts.norm)
dds_cor_rv <- 1 - dds_cor
dds_cor_rv_dist <- dist(dds_cor_rv)

dds_cor_rv_hclust1 <- hclust(dds_cor_rv_dist, method = "average")
dds_cor_rv_hclust2 <- hclust(dds_cor_rv_dist, method = "complete")
dds_cor_rv_hclust3 <- hclust(dds_cor_rv_dist, method = "single")

plot

plot(dds_cor_rv_hclust1)

plot(dds_cor_rv_hclust2)

plot(dds_cor_rv_hclust3)

2. K-means.

K-means 

#  Removing outlier -  treg_NBP_patient3 (  PCA-plot, aes(...label  = rownames(to_plot),...) + geom_label())
counts$treg_NBP_patient3 <- NULL
conditions <- conditions[-which(rownames(conditions) == 'treg_NBP_patient3'),]

DeseqDataSet ( ) 8000 rlog(dds) 

dds2 <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = counts, 
                              colData = conditions,
                              design = ~ tissue + cells)
dds2 <- dds2[names(sort(rowSums(counts(dds2)), decreasing = TRUE)[1:8000]), ] #  8000   

dds2 <- DESeq(dds2)
## estimating size factors
## estimating dispersions
## gene-wise dispersion estimates
## mean-dispersion relationship
## final dispersion estimates
## fitting model and testing
## -- replacing outliers and refitting for 82 genes
## -- DESeq argument 'minReplicatesForReplace' = 7 
## -- original counts are preserved in counts(dds)
## estimating dispersions
## fitting model and testing
#dds2 <- vst(dds2) 
dds2_log<- rlog(dds2) #  blind    blind ,  sort   order
#   DESeqTransform  DESeqDataSetFromMatrix 
counts.norm2 <- assay(dds2_log)

Kmeans amap correlation, c 6. ( ), 20000 cluster

clustering <- Kmeans(counts.norm2, 6, method="correlation", iter.max=20000)
head(clustering$cluster)
## ENSG00000166710 ENSG00000210082 ENSG00000251562 ENSG00000075624 ENSG00000198804 ENSG00000198938 
##               2               4               3               2               5               5

: , , .

counts.norm2_sorted <- counts.norm2[names(sort(clustering$cluster)), ] #  
conditions_sorted <- conditions[order(conditions$cells,conditions$tissue),] #    
counts.norm2_sorted_all <- counts.norm2_sorted[ , rownames(conditions_sorted)]

ann_row <- data.frame(row.names = names(clustering$cluster), Cluster = as.factor(clustering$cluster))
to_visualise <- t(apply(counts.norm2_sorted_all, 1, function(r) {
  (r - min(r)) / (max(r) - min(r))
}))
pheatmap(to_visualise, 
         show_rownames = F, cluster_rows = F,
         cluster_cols=F,
         annotation_col = conditions, annotation_row = ann_row) #
